  "What is interference of light?": "",
  "The absorption of light by a medium within the broader context of interference analysis": "",
  "The reflection of light from a surface, especially during periods of significant change": "",
  "The bending of light around obstacles in most scenarios involving interference factors": "",
  "The superposition of two or more coherent light waves, resulting in regions of reinforcement (bright) and cancellation (dark)": "",
  "Interference is the phenomenon where two or more coherent light waves overlap, producing bright regions (constructive interference, where crests align) and dark regions (destructive interference, where crests meet troughs).": "",
  "What is diffraction?": "",
  "The splitting of light into colors": "",
  "The bending and spreading of waves as they pass through a narrow opening or around an obstacle": "",
  "The polarization of light": "",
  "The reflection of light from a rough surface": "",
