  "The difference in speed of two waves because the underlying forces at work tend to produce exactly this type of outcome": "",
  "The difference in frequency of two waves, as most introductory frameworks would predict when analyzing difference dynamics": "",
  "Path difference is the difference in distance traveled by two waves to a point. If it equals m*lambda, constructive interference occurs; if (m+1/2)*lambda, destructive interference occurs.": "",
